<materialsCitation box="[1987,2165,1033,1066]" pageId="16" pageNumber="265">“Costa Rica.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[1986,2580,1002,1421]" pageId="16" pageNumber="265">
Placed into subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1895" box="[2315,2482,1072,1105]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Macrogeomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Macrogeomys</taxonomicName>
. Heterogeomys considered a subgenus of Orthogeomys by J. L. Patton in 2005 but was resurrected to genus status by T. A. Spradling and colleagues in 2016. Molecular studies suggest that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1865" box="[2163,2323,1269,1302]" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Geomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heterodus">H. heterodus</taxonomicName>
is sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J.A.Allen" authorityYear="1893" class="Mammalia" family="Geomyidae" genus="Heterogeomys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="16" pageNumber="265" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cherriei">H. cherriei</taxonomicName>
. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
